OL,6,FOn the decision not to progress with
OL,7,Fthe plans, Leader of the Council,
OL,8,FCouncillor Mark Pritchard, said: "I
OL,9,Fwould like to thank the Home Office
OL,10,Ffor their response and I am glad that
OL,11,Fthe right decision has been made and
OL,12,Fcommon sense has prevailed in this
OL,13,Finstance."
OL,15,FDeputy Leader, Councillor David A
OL,16,FBithell, said: "I hope this will
OL,17,Freassure the residents of
OL,18,FRhosllanerchrugog of a positive
OL,19,Foutcome to address their concerns."
